    <segment id="1" parent="2" relname="background">
Consistency and standards are one of the ten Nielsen&apos;s ten usability heuristics.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="10" relname="span"> Mr. 
Barnum defines consistency and standards as the user not having to wonder whether 
different actions mean the same thing.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="3" relname="span"> Microsoft office XP suite is an example of 
consistency.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="8" relname="span"> Access, Excel, and PowerPoint have similar standard and formatting menu.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="9" relname="span">  
If a user knows how to use the menus from one of the programs, the user will not have 
problems using the menus from the other programs.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="6" relname="evaluation">  This also makes it easy for users to 
learn the software&apos;s.</segment>
